                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d375">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/3963: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Lithuania</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Norem</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kaunas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-18T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 18, 1940—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 2:43 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>119. Occupation movements continue with Soviet units being moved towards German
                    border. Estimated number of Russian troops 300,000. Populace remains quietly at
                    work. Banks report normal turnover. Rumors of German concentrations seem well
                    substantiated. Jewish inhabitants moving away from western cities.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Moscow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Norem</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
